            <svg class="h-4 w-4 mr-2 text-success" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 8V4H8"/><rect width="16" height="12" x="4" y="8" rx="2"/><path d="M2 14h2"/><path d="M20 14h2"/><path d="M15 13v2"/><path d="M9 13v2"/></svg>
            4 Major AI Search Platforms
          </span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center">
            <svg class="h-4 w-4 mr-2 text-success" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg>
            Schema-Powered Citations
          </span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center">
            <svg class="h-4 w-4 mr-2 text-success" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"/><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"/></svg>
            Future-Proof Visibility
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 space-y-20">

      <!-- What Is AI Search Optimization -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">What Is AI Search Optimization?</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-muted-foreground space-y-6">
          <p>
            AI Search Optimization is the practice of making your content citation-worthy for AI-powered search engines. While traditional SEO focuses on ranking in search results, AI search optimization focuses on being the answer that platforms like Google SGE, Microsoft Copilot, Perplexity, and ChatGPT cite as authoritative sources.
          </p>
          <p>
            The shift is fundamental: users aren't clicking through 10 blue links anymore. They're asking AI engines for answers and trusting the sources AI cites. If your content isn't optimized for AI understanding, you're invisible to this massive and growing audience.
          </p>

          <!-- Comparison Table -->
          <div class="my-8 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-border">
            <table class="w-full">
              <thead class="bg-muted">
                <tr>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold">Aspect</th>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold">Traditional Search</th>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold">AI Search</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-border">
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 font-medium">User Behavior</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4">Click through results</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4">Get instant answers</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 font-medium">Success Metric</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4">Ranking position</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4">Being cited as source</td>
